 Each element i of the output should will be 'the number of odd elements in the 
 string i of the input." where all the i's should will be replace by the number 
 of odd digits in the i'th string of the input.

>>> odd_count({"1234567"})
{'the number of odd elements 4n the str4ng 4 of the 4nput."}
>>> odd_count({"3","11111111"})
